article.headline: Illinois St. 60, S. Illinois 40
article.story: NORMAL, Ill. -- Jackie Carmichael had 19 points and 11 rebounds Saturday as Illinois State beat Southern Illinois 60-40. John Wilkins scored 10 points and matched Carmichael with 11 boards -- tying Wilkins' career high -- for the Redbirds (14-8, 6-5 Missouri Valley). Carmichael and Wilkins each blocked three SIU shots. ISU led 26-17 at halftime and ran off 16 straight points during a 9-minute stretch in the second half to put it out of reach. Jeff Early and Taylor Diamond had 10 points to lead the Salukis (7-15, 4-7), who shot 30 percent from the field. The 40 points is a season low for SIU. The Salukis scored 42 at Wichita State a week ago.
